The blue city in Afghanistan was once almost completely shut off from the outside world but is now trying to find a balance between formidable history and friendly people. Founded 1200 years ago, the ‘blue city’ of Afghanistan now gives the name to an NGO-run hospital, a scrap metal shop and a carpet store that feature this particular shade, and the old towering statues of the Knights of Kabul Nowhere is the clash between old and new more pronounced than in downtown Kabul, home to Afghanistan’s presidential palace,
